      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:3:32:2",
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) الْمَعْرِفَةُ مِنْ صُنْعِ مَنْ هِيَ قَالَ مِنْ صُنْعِ اللَّهِ لَيْسَ لِلْعِبَادِ فِيهَا صُنْعٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya and someone else, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Muhammad Bin Abu Umeyr, from Muhammad Bin Hakeym who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, ‘The recognition (الْمَعْرِفَةُ) from a maker, whose is it?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘From the Making of Allah<sup>azwj</sup>. There isn’t for the servants, a making with regards to it’."
        ]
      }
    }
